8:["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"What This Is"}]
9:["$","p",null,{"children":"Creatrweb is a portable kit of context files that guides AI coding agents toward creative, human-steered, IndieWeb-aligned development. It works across Gemini CLI, Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, and GitHub Copilot from a single source of truth."}]
a:["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"16px"},"children":"The framework applies three principles consistently across every AI tool you use:"}]
b:["$","ul",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px","paddingLeft":"20px","lineHeight":"2"},"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Human ownership"}]," — the agent asks before building, shows options before committing, and stops at irreversible decisions."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Distinct voice"}]," — gallery-format choices resist AI averaging. Research shows human-steered sessions produce outcomes 2–4× better than passive ones."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"IndieWeb longevity"}]," — your content stays portable, your URLs never break, and every dependency is documented."]}]]}]
c:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"Repository Structure"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Place these files at the root of every new project before your first agent session:"}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"your-project/\n├── AGENTS.md                  ← Main instruction file (all agents)\n├── CLAUDE.md                  ← Claude Code entry point\n├── CONSTRAINTS.md             ← Active project constraints (starts empty)\n├── DECISIONS.md               ← Architecture log (agent fills during sessions)\n├── .env.example               ← Environment variable reference\n├── .gemini/\n│   └── settings.json          ← Gemini CLI context configuration\n└── docs/\n    └── eval-prompt.md         ← Optional: post-session compliance audit"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"16px"},"children":"Files the agent creates during sessions — do not create manually:"}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"MEMORY.md                      ← Confirmed lessons (agent proposes, you approve)\ndocs/dependencies.md           ← Vendor dependency registry (agent maintains)"}]]}]
d:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"Setup — New Project"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Step 1 — Copy the kit"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Copy all files from this template into your project root. No configuration required before your first session."}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Step 2 — Fill in the Project Profile (optional)"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Open ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," and find the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Project Profile"}]," section near the top. If you know what you are building, fill in the four fields at an architecture level — no technical details required:"]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"Deployment: Node.js PaaS, single process, npm start\nDatabase:   SQLite via Drizzle ORM\nVersion pins: Node 20, Next.js 15.x\nStack:      Next.js + TypeScript"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"If you leave this blank, the agent will ask you three plain-language questions at the start of the first session and fill it in for you."}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Step 3 — Set up your environment"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Copy ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env.example"}]," to ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env"}]," and fill in any values your project needs. Never commit ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env"}]," to version control — it is in ",["$","code",null,{"children":".gitignore"}]," by default."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Step 4 — Start your first session"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Open your chosen agent tool in the project directory and begin. The agent reads",["$","code",null,{"children":" AGENTS.md"}]," automatically. No special prompt is required for the first session — it will ask one question to confirm the current phase before writing any code."]}]]}]
e:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"File Reference"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"AGENTS.md"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The authoritative instruction file. Read by every agent on every session start. Contains the Six Rules that override all agent defaults, Brainstorm Mode for open-ended exploration, gallery protocol for design decisions, IndieWeb specifications and POSSE rules, and memory file management."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Do not edit during a session."}]," Only the project owner changes this file. The agent will propose changes as a diff and wait for approval."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"CLAUDE.md"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["A one-line file that imports ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," into Claude Code. Claude Code reads",["$","code",null,{"children":" CLAUDE.md"}]," natively — this file ensures it gets the full AGENTS.md ruleset without duplication. Add any Claude-specific instructions below the import line."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"CONSTRAINTS.md"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Starts empty. The agent creates an entry here the first time you state a constraint during any session — licensing requirements, data privacy rules, dependency restrictions, anything binding. Constraints are permanent until you explicitly lift them."}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"CONSTRAINT: No third-party analytics or tracking scripts\nSCOPE:      All pages and API routes\nSET:        YYYY-MM-DD"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"DECISIONS.md"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Starts as a template with a Project Profile and phase sections. The agent fills in each section during sessions — you never need to write to this file directly. It becomes the persistent audit trail for every architectural decision made across all phases and tools."}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":".env.example"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["A reference file showing which environment variable names the project requires. Contains no values — only names. Copy to ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env"}]," and fill in values locally."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":".gemini/settings.json"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Required for Gemini CLI. Without it, Gemini ignores ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," and uses its own defaults. This file points Gemini at the correct context files:"]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"{\n  \"context\": {\n    \"files\": [\n      \"AGENTS.md\",\n      \"CONSTRAINTS.md\",\n      \"MEMORY.md\"\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"EVALUATE_PROMPT.md"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Not read automatically. Use it at the end of any session to run a structured compliance audit. Paste the file's contents into the same tool that just completed the session, or into a separate analysis session with the chat log attached."}]]}]
f:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"Agent-by-Agent Guide"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Codex CLI"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Phase 1 scaffolding, schema design, initial file structure, and any work where you want strict question-before-build discipline with full terminal access."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":["Natively reads ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," from the project root. No configuration needed. Follows Rule 1 (ask before building) most consistently of all the tools."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Tip:"}]," Start each Codex session with a ",["$","code",null,{"children":"SESSION CONSTRAINTS"}]," block in your opening prompt listing phase-specific rules."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Gemini CLI"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," UI components, interactive feature development, and sessions where you want rapid iteration with gallery-style design choices."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":["Requires ",["$","code",null,{"children":".gemini/settings.json"}]," to read ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}],". Without this file, Gemini uses its own defaults and ignores the framework entirely. The gallery protocol (Rule 2) is where Gemini performs best."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Known limitation:"}]," Reference sections are read at session start but not actively consulted during code generation. Use a ",["$","code",null,{"children":"SESSION CONSTRAINTS"}]," block to promote critical rules into active context."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Claude Code"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Refactoring, cross-file consistency, spec implementation (Webmention, IndieAuth, Micropub), and sessions requiring strong instruction-following across many files."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":["Reads ",["$","code",null,{"children":"CLAUDE.md"}]," natively. ",["$","code",null,{"children":"CLAUDE.md"}]," imports ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," with"," ",["$","code",null,{"children":"@AGENTS.md"}],", so the full ruleset loads automatically. Handles the Irreversible Decisions checkpoints more reliably than other tools."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"Cursor (Chat and Composer)"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Day-to-day feature work, inline edits, and sessions where you want suggestions before auto-apply."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":["Reads ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," natively in Chat and Composer modes. In Cursor Composer, ask for a plan first — the plan output will naturally take gallery form if AGENTS.md is in context, giving you three options before any code is written."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"readme_subSection__tsf_p","children":"GitHub Copilot (Chat)"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," In-editor assistance, quick completions, and sessions where the human is driving and wants suggestions rather than autonomous building."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"8px"},"children":["Reads ",["$","code",null,{"children":"AGENTS.md"}]," as a repository instruction file. Best suited for asking questions about the codebase and getting targeted help on a single file or function. Treat its suggestions as proposals, not decisions — review before accepting."]}]]}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"How the Files Work Together Across Sessions"}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"readme_codeBlock__Q03X7","children":"Session 1 (e.g. Codex CLI)\n  └── Reads: AGENTS.md\n  └── Creates: DECISIONS.md (Phase 1), CONSTRAINTS.md (if constraints stated)\n  └── Proposes: MEMORY.md entries at session end\n\nSession 2 (e.g. Gemini CLI)\n  └── Reads: AGENTS.md + CONSTRAINTS.md + MEMORY.md (via settings.json)\n  └── Appends: DECISIONS.md (Phase 2)\n  └── Inherits all constraints and confirmed lessons automatically\n\nSession 3 (e.g. Cursor or Claude Code)\n  └── Reads: AGENTS.md + CONSTRAINTS.md + MEMORY.md\n  └── Resolves: unresolved checkpoints from DECISIONS.md\n  └── Continues without repeating Phase 1–2 decisions"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"No tool ever needs to be told what was decided in a prior session — the memory files carry that context automatically."}]]}]
11:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"Post-Session Compliance Audit"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"At the end of any session, run the eval prompt to check how well the agent followed AGENTS.md:"}],["$","ol",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px","paddingLeft":"20px","lineHeight":"2"},"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":["Open ",["$","code",null,{"children":"EVALUATE_PROMPT.md"}]]}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Paste its contents into the tool that just completed the session, or into a separate analysis session with the chat log attached"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Review the Pass / Partial / Fail scores"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Apply only the recommended changes that would have prevented an actual failure — not changes for rules already followed"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"The final section of the eval prompt asks the agent to recommend AGENTS.md or CONSTRAINTS.md changes. This is the feedback loop that improves the framework over time based on real failures."}]]}]
12:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"Known Behavioral Limitation"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The gallery protocol (Rule 2 — show 2–3 options before committing) is the framework's primary mechanism for preserving human creative ownership. It fires reliably when a prompt is exploratory or open-ended. It is suppressed when a prompt contains specific measurements, named files, or exact values — because the agent correctly reads those details as a directive and executes rather than offering alternatives."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"This is a model-level inference pattern. It cannot be resolved in AGENTS.md — adding more rules does not improve adherence when the suppression comes from the prompt signal itself."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"Both modes are valid. If you want options, write an open prompt:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"readme_promptExample__SwovY","children":"\"The terminal dialog feels cramped on mobile. What are some approaches?\""}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"If you want execution, write a specific prompt:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"readme_promptExample__SwovY","children":"\"Reduce the terminal dialog padding to 24px on mobile.\""}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":"The framework respects your signal. If you write a specific prompt and later wish you had seen options, run the eval prompt at session end — the agent will identify the missed gallery opportunity and log it."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":["Over time, ",["$","code",null,{"children":"MEMORY.md"}]," accumulates your aesthetic preferences so future sessions need fewer explicit options to reflect your direction accurately."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"12px"},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"For Claude Code users:"}]," This behavior is addressed proactively in"," ",["$","code",null,{"children":"CLAUDE.md"}],". When Claude Code is in Plan Mode and detects a high-specificity prompt, it is instructed to name the suppression at the top of the plan and offer one alternative framing before building. The eval prompt remains the recovery mechanism for sessions where suppression was not caught in time."]}]]}]
13:["$","section",null,{"className":"project-detail_section__WzfAr","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"project-detail_sectionTitle__nXjlE","children":"IndieWeb Quick Reference"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"This framework is built around IndieWeb principles. Build specifications in priority order — do not implement a spec until a real user need depends on it."}],["$","table",null,{"className":"readme_table__vgzT3","style":{"marginTop":"20px"},"children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","th",null,{"children":"Priority"}],["$","th",null,{"children":"Spec"}],["$","th",null,{"children":"What it does"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"children":[["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"1"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"rel=me"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Links your domain to your profiles elsewhere"}]]}],["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"1"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"microformats2"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Makes your content machine-readable without breaking HTML"}]]}],["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"2"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"Webmention"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Lets other sites notify you when they link to you"}]]}],["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"2"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"IndieAuth"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Makes your domain an identity provider"}]]}],["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"3"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"Micropub"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Lets external apps publish to your site"}]]}],["$","tr",null,{"children":[["$","td",null,{"children":"4"}],["$","td",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"className":"readme_badge__AtiRr","children":"WebSub"}]}],["$","td",null,{"children":"Pushes new content to subscribers in real time"}]]}]]}]]}]]}]
